                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d321">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandam received at the Department of State from Mr.
                        Wu.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chinese Legation</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-08-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 21, 1900</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="italic">Cablegram from Viceroy Li Hung Chang, dated August 21, 1900,
                        and received by Minister Wu on the same day.</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The Boxer rebels in Pekin having been dispersed, there will be positively no more
                    fighting. Further military operations on the part of the powers are greatly to
                    be deplored. Besides urging cessation of hostilities, please confer with
                    Secretary of State upon subject of withdrawal of troops and appointment of
                    plenipotentiary to negotiate settlement of all other questions so as to preserve
                    amicable relations. I await early reply.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
